        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 2:23PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 223 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northwest of Tecolote, or 12 miles southwest of Las Vegas,
moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tecolote, Romeroville, Ojitos Frios, San Pablo and San Geronimo.

This includes the following highways...
State Road 283 between Mile Markers 2 and 10.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 326 and 327...and
between Mile Markers 335 and 342.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Accumulations of small hail on roads can create very slick and
hazardous driving conditions.</instruction>
